p: Similar to the observations in adult mice (Fig. 2a), a single immunization of neonatal mice with 10 10 vp Ad26.RSV.preF resulted in high VNA titers with antibodies binding to the F protein in both its prefusion and postfusion conformation, whereas immunization with FI-RSV resulted in no detectable VNA titers, and hardly any prefusion F-binding antibodies (Fig. 3a). PostF-specific binding antibodies induced by Ad26.RSV.preF in neonatal mice were of both IgG1 and IgG2a subclasses. In contrast, FI-RSV induced only RSV F-specific IgG1 antibodies but no detectable IgG2a antibodies, indicative of a Th2-biased profile (Fig. 5a).
